column.name: content
column.value:
Welcome!

 

Eagle Hotel is a hotel in a superb 17th Century house built as the home of the 3rd Earl of Ladegaard. The charismatic 3rd Earl of Ladegaard lived here for more than 40 years until his death in 1705. The 17th Century house has been in the Ladegaard family ever since. In 1869 the house was beautifully restored and opened as a luxury hotel and you can now enjoy the truly magnificent surroundings of the house.

 

We invite you to stay at Eagle Hotel where a warm welcome awaits you. Our friendly staff will do their very best to ensure that your stay here will be an oasis of calm and relaxation. We hope you will enjoy your stay!

column.name: content
column.value:
Rooms

 

All 25 rooms at Eagle Hotel are elegant and well appointed. Each room has a spacious and comfortable en-suite bathroom with a shower and a bath.

 

Room Amenities

Bathrobe and slippers are provided for your comfort during your stay. Complimentary toiletries include shampoo, conditioner, bathing soap, body lotion, nail file and sewing kit. Additionally all rooms are fitted with a radio, a CD player, cable/satellite TV,  ISDN/modem and a direct telephone line.  You can also enjoy drinks from your minibar and coffee/tea from your tea making facilities. Finally every room has a balcony with wonderful views and we bring your complimentary morning paper to your airconditioned room every morning.


 

Room types

 

Single Room

Our single rooms are comfortably and stylishly decorated. The rooms have a single bed for one person with luxurious fabrics. All single rooms are spacious with at least 15 square meters.

 

Double Room

Our double rooms are individually designed complete with luxurious en-suite bathrooms. The double rooms have a queen bed. The fabrics are luxurious and the room spacious with more than 24 square meters.

 

Twin Room

Our twin rooms are bright and airy with large windows and with elegant en-suite bathrooms. The twin rooms have two single beds. The twin rooms also have a writing desk and comfortable armchairs.

 

Junior Suite

Our junior suites are exquisitely designed to create a stylish and comfortable environment. The junior suites have 1 queen bed and 1 single bed. In addition there is an elegant sitting area where you can relax. Junior suites are generous in size with up to 50 square meters.


 

Deluxe suite

Our deluxe suites have all state-of-the-art facilities. There are 2 king beds and a separate stylish sitting room with a magnificent view. They are all in excess of 70 square meters.

column.name: content
column.value:
Facilities

 

 

Bar

Come and enjoy our atmospheric bar at Eagle Hotel. We serve top-notch wines and imaginative cocktails.
 

Croquet Lawn

Play a game of croquet while enjoying the scent of roses on our impeccably maintained quality lawn. All necessary croquet equipment is available.

 

 

Fishing

The rivers near Eagle Hotel offer excellent fishing opportunities. Fishing gear is available at the hotel.

 

Fitness Center

We offer you the finest and most advanced range of fitness equipment in our fitness center. Come and enjoy a healthier lifestyle.

 

 

Garden/Terrace

Our garden is one of the country's most beautifully kept landscaped garden. Come and sit in our garden and enjoy an oasis of tranquility.

 

Golf

Our private 18-hole golf course is open to everyone staying at our hotel. The course is heath land and there is an abundance of trees, which makes the course a little more difficult than average.

 

 

Horse Riding

The countryside around Eagle Hotel is great for horse riding with wonderful forest and spectacular scenery.

 

Indoor Swimming Pool

Relax in our 17 meter indoor swimming pool and its luxurious surroundings.

 

 

Outdoor Swimming Pool

Our heated outdoor swimming pool allows you to chill out in magnificent surroundings.

 

Private beach

Indulge yourself on our private sandy beach located quietly away from the crowds.

 

 

Restaurant

We will be pleased to serve you the best authentic French cuisine in our stylish 5-star restaurant.

 

Sauna

Follow in the footsteps of the Finnish. Remove your stress in the relaxing atmosphere of our sauna.

 
 

Shooting

Make your stay at Eagle Hotel a recreational highlight with the excitement of shooting clay pigeons. Lessons are available upon request.

 

Spa

Our spa is a haven of well being and serenity, where mind and body are relaxed and soothed by dedicated and professional staff.

 

 

Tennis

In the heart of our grounds we have 3 hard floodlit tennis courts.

 

Watersports

There are plenty of choices of activity for the watersport enthusiast. Our most popular activities are diving, kayaking, water-skiing and windsurfing.

 

 

Wintersports

The location of Eagle Hotel makes it an ideal base for wintersport activities. Enjoy the excitement of great skiing and snowboarding.

Location

 

Eagle Hotel is located approximately 3 miles east of Mystery Village.

 

By Car

Leave the M99 motorway at junction 8 and follow the signs for Fairytale Valley. Once in Fairytale Valley turn right at the crossroads to Mystery Village and Eagle Hotel is on your left hand side after approximately 3 miles.

By Air

Nearest airport is Central City airport. There are taxis at the airport, which can take you the 15 miles to Eagle Hotel.

By Rail

Nearest train station is in Mystery Village. There are taxis at the station, which can take you the 3 miles to Eagle Hotel.

News

 

09.12 - Visit from celebrity chef Francois Curie

We are extremely lucky and pleased to introduce celebrity chef Francois Curie into our kitchen for 4 special gourmet evenings. Francois has created a unique 3-course dinner over the theme Golf & Forest for this occasion. The menu consists of

 

 

Brestogne Cream Mushroom Soup

Roasted Phesant with Cranberry Sauce and Roasted Sweet Potato

Petit Fours with Coffee and Tea ad libitum

 

The price for this spectacular evening is £69. Dates and times will be announced later, but to make a prelimenary booking please call us.


 

25.11 - State-of-the-art Multimedia in all Rooms

We have now completed a complete refurbishment of our rooms. The refurbishment includes the addition of advanced multimedia technology in all rooms. This includes state-of-the-art DVD-player and television and instant access to the internet. The refurbishment was completed with the help of StateArt Technology.


 

 

17.10 - Valentines Packages Now on Sale

Please see our Special Offers page for more details.

Brestogne Cream Mushroom Soup

Roasted Phesant with Cranberry Sauce and Roasted Sweet Potato

Petit Fours with Coffee and Tea ad libitum

 

The price for this spectacular evening is £69. Dates and times will be announced later, but to make a prelimenary booking please call us.


 

25.11 - State-of-the-art Multimedia in all Rooms

We have now completed a complete refurbishment of our rooms. The refurbishment includes the addition of advanced multimedia technology in all rooms. This includes state-of-the-art DVD-player and television and instant access to the internet. The refurbishment was completed with the help of StateArt Technology.


 

 

17.10 - Valentines Packages Now on Sale

Please see our Special Offers page for more details.

This is one of the most splendid landscaped gardens of the 18th century. It's stunning formal layout complemented by informal planting in bright colors and situated in a rocky setting is brilliant and offers a feeling of variety and adventure for the visitor. There are more than 300 species of trees and more than 1200 species of rare lower to be enjoyed by the visitor. The three lakes is a sanctuary for the many rare birds and around 30 different species of fish. There is also a deer enclosure with more than 300 deer.

The gardens designed to be beautiful all year round and there are three routes of varying degrees of difficulty, which will take you round the garden. The easy route is 7 miles and is accessible for wheelchairs. The medium route is 11 miles and the long route is 14 miles and takes you round the entire rock plateau and all three lakes.

column.name: col2
column.value:
The Ashott Racing Course is the host to some of the best flat races. The course opens in March with the legendary Davon meeting and closes with the Eden meeting in late October. The Racing Course is surrounded by magnificent nature on the borders of the Catswold Downs. The Racing Course itself is of the highest quality and is approximately 1 mile long.

The Ashott Racing Course also comprises one of of the world's most extensive training grounds. There are more than 1500 racehorses, around 50 licensed trainers and in excess of 45 stud farms where the racehorses of the future are bred.

column.name: col3
column.value: Leading horse racing course with some of the best flat races.

column.name: col2
column.value:
The Marble Church is more than 800 years old. The first stone of the church was laid by King Hans V in 1126. In 1140 the work was stopped because of economical difficulties, but was restarted again in the late 14th Century on the intiative of one of Made's most prominent businessmen, Dietgen. The church was finally inaugurated in 1594.

The real name of the Marble Church is actually Hanschurch, but because of the marble, which adorns the church it is better known as the Marble Church. The church is dominated by a big dome that can be seen from 50 miles away.

The church has been the setting of many important historic events. It was here that King Peter was killed in 1751 and in 1895 the poet Mark Histaric was married to Helena Daskil.

column.name: col3
column.value: Historic church, which is more than 800 years old.

column.name: col2
column.value:
The High Beach Waterpark has provided thrilling entertainment for adults and children alike for more than 15 years. The waterpark consists of two distinct areas. The Splash Park and the Castle Park.

The Splash Park is the place of action with over 2 miles of water adventures, 4 children's water playgrounds and 21 water slides. The High Bach Waterpark prides itself of the tropical setting of its attractions with palm trees and clean white sand everywhere for your full enjoyment.

The Castle Park is a place of relaxation with 100ha of beautiful nature and plenty of restaurants and cafes where you can enjoy delicious meals. There are also 3 well stocked souvenier shops where you can buy something to remind you of the excitement of the High Beach Waterpark and there are plenty of other activities.

column.name: col3
column.value: Waterpark with more than 41 thrilling water rides.

column.name: col2
column.value:
Watersports & Activity centre open 7 days a week for the enthusiast as well as the beginner. There is water skiing, sailing, kayaking and you can hire boats. Good changing and shower facilities. You don't have to be a member to use the facilities. Friendly staff is available to help you at any time.

You can also hire boats for water skiing and buy lessons to improve your skills. All ages are taught and the latest and safest equipment is used. Equipment is also inspected regularly.

There is also a restaurant with refreshments onsite and not to forget this is a place of outstanding beauty with the backdrop of the Glencairn Hills.

column.name: col3
column.value: Watersports centre with water skiing, sailing, kayaking and boat hire.

column.name: col4
column.value: No admission charge for the centre. Charges for rental of boats and windsurfing equipment.

column.name: col2
column.value:
World class maritime museum. The permanent exhibition includes more than 50 historic vessels. The wide variety of vessels represented includes container ships, ocean liners, aircraft carriers, warships, passenger ships and fishing boats.

The most famous of our vessels is the 150 year old Feodora, which became known as one of the fastest and most evasive pirate ships there have ever been. The Feodora is a magnificent 3 mast sailing ship built in quality materials by the King of Maden. In 1902 pirates boarded the ship on its way to East India and threw the entire crew into the water. It was not recaptured again until 1967.

The museum also dedicates a large proportion of the exhibition space to teaching children about the sea and maritime life in general. The museum often has temporary exhibitions. In the past there have been temporary exhibitions about model ships, navy uniforms and about freak waves.

column.name: col3
column.value: Internationally renowned maritime museum with more than 50 historic vessels on display.

column.name: col2
column.value:
Whitewalls Palace is a 4-storey old 18th-century rococo/baroque mansion situated in Ramblas Forest. There are four wings with a total of 34 rooms. The mansion is home to many interesting paintings and porcelain from the 19th century.

It was built by Ben Virreija between 1774 and 1778 for the viceroy Amant Virou. The Curiously white walls have given the mansion its name. The viceroy wanted white walls to reflect the winter landscape, which typically surrounds the mansion in December and January.

Today the Whitewalls Palace has a number of exhibition halls, a culture information centre, an Art & Books shop and a ticket office. There are also 300ha of landscaped gardens and a tea room.

Silverland Adventure Park has more than 50 attractions including 10 thrilling rollercoaster rides. There are also a number of quiet rides for younger children and arcades and games including fortune wheels, shooting galleries and ball throwing games.

There is also a big area with slot machines where you can win cash prizes.  If you are hungry there are a wide range of refreshment options. There is fastfood for a quick meal and a number of restaurants with cuisines from all around the world if you prefer to spend more time enjoying a proper meal.

The highlight every evening is the entertainment. The entertainment is usually a combination of jazz concerts, acrobats or similar with no extra charge.
